The Liver Cancer Immune Microenvironment: Therapeutic Implications for Hepatocellular Carcinoma.
Other immune targeting-strategies, such as adoptive T-cell transfer, vaccination, or virotherapy, are currently under development. This review provides an overview on the HCC immune microenvironment, the different cellular players, the current available immunotherapies, and potential immunotherapy modalities.
